<br>
As the above poster mentioned, one of the reasons is because it doesn't run a full-blown OS and tons of idle programs all the time.<br>
<br>
Plus on top of that, every game made for the XBox is optimized for the RAM, the specific video card used, the sound, etc.<br>
<br>
PCs are at a disadvantage because there are too many variables for what may be in the PC (plus the fact that any game you buy still have to be able to run on a 32 MB video card).  Programmers aren't allowed to optimize anything specific and that's why you see better graphics on consoles (that also goes for PS2 and GC). <p>The surest sign of intelligent life in the universe is that none<BR>of it has tried contacting us.<BR>

