Do you know how RAM works?  That's not the problem... The problem is that game programmers have to factor in too many variables for PC gaming (such as slower hardware, less RAM, cheap video cards) while programmers for XBox are given a stable platform to work with, thereby allowing them to take the graphics and go all-out with them.  Also factor in that most peoples' TVs are 27&quot; or bigger while most monitors are 19&quot; or smaller.  Sure, the graphics LOOK better, but they're really not. <p>The surest sign of intelligent life in the universe is that none<BR>of it has tried contacting us.<BR>

